CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 8, 1958, pg. A12 reads: "Celebrate First Anniversary - The first anniversary of Heroines of Jericho, Mozella Court 7, OES, was celebrated with an elaborate dinner held at North Side Elks. Left to right are Bro. Herbert Townes, Marion [Miriam] Fountain, Sister Esther Green, Grand Matron; Gertrude Campbell and Clara Randolph, who was mistress of ceremonies.  Standing are Edmonia Stevens, Helen M. Lawrence, M.A. Matron; Morris Fountain, Christine Knight, Mary Smith and Leo McTurner, Exalted Ruler of the North Side Elks. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Elks members, seated from left: Herbert Townes, Miriam Sharpe Fountain, Esther Green, Gertrude Campbell, and Clara Randolph; standing: Edmonia Stevens, Helen M. Lawrence, Morris Fountain, Christine Knight, Mary Smith, and Leo McTurner, gathered for first anniversary of Heroines of Jericho, Mozella Court 7, OES dinner, North Side Elks, another version
